# Claude Sentient — Cursor Rules

This project uses Claude Sentient, an autonomous development orchestration layer.

## Core Conventions

### Code Quality
- Function max 50 lines, cyclomatic complexity ≤ 10, nesting depth ≤ 3
- No magic numbers — use named constants
- Early returns over nested conditionals
- No debug/console.log left in committed code

### Error Handling
- Always propagate errors explicitly (never swallow with empty catch)
- Wrap errors with context: "doing X: {err}"
- Map errors to appropriate output types at boundaries

### Testing
- Write tests for new functionality before considering work done
- Table-driven / parameterized tests for multiple cases
- Test files mirror source structure

### Git
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`
- Quality gates before commit: lint → test → build
- Never commit with failing tests

## Project Structure

```
.claude/commands/    # /cs-* slash commands
.claude/hooks/       # Session lifecycle hooks (.cjs)
.claude/rules/       # Always-loaded and path-scoped rules
agents/              # Agent role definitions (YAML + MD)
profiles/            # Language profiles (YAML)
schemas/             # JSON schemas for validation
examples/            # Project CLAUDE.md templates
```

## Running Quality Gates

```bash
# Shell profile (default for this project)
shellcheck install.sh uninstall.sh generate-checksums.sh

# All tests
node profiles/__tests__/test-profiles.js
node .claude/hooks/__tests__/test-hooks.js
node .claude/commands/__tests__/test-commands.js
node agents/__tests__/test-agents.js
node schemas/__tests__/test-schemas.js
node integration/__tests__/test-integration.js
```

## Key Files

- `CLAUDE.md` — Project overview and commands reference
- `CHANGELOG.md` — Version history
- `STATUS.md` — Current development state
- `DECISIONS.md` — Architecture decision records
- `.claude/rules/learnings.md` — Captured decisions and learnings
